This paper deals with distributional semantic models, which are commonly used in natural language processing and information retrieval, suggesting that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also discusses machine learning methods such as Support Vector Machines, which are relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of iterative term set expansion methods is also relevant to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. The paper's focus on comparing different methods for term set expansion suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper's empirical study of the performance of different methods suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
